05669nam a22009015i 9783110539516DE-B159720230228123812.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||230228t20172017gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97831105395167 a10.1515/97831105395162doi  a(DE-B1597)479503  a(OCoLC)1002222240  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 7aLAN0090002bisacsh1 aStolz, Thomas, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aSpatial Interrogatives in Europe and Beyond :bWhere, Whither, Whence /cThomas Stolz, Nataliya Levkovych, Aina Urdze, Julia Nintemann, Maja Robbers. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter Mouton, c[2017] 4c©2017  a1 online resource (XLIII, 733 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aStudia Typologica [STTYP] : Beihefte / Supplements STUF - Sprachtypologie und Universalienforschung / Language Typology and Universals ,x1617-2957 ;v2000tFrontmatter -- tPreface and Acknowledgments -- tContents -- tList of Abbreviations -- tList of Diagrams -- tList of Schemes -- tList of Tables -- t1. Introduction -- t2. The formal relations of spatial interrogatives -- t3. WHERE, WHITHER, and WHENCE in the languages of Europe -- t4. The big world -- t5. Spatial relations across sentence-types -- t6. Conclusions -- tSources -- tAppendix: Language sample -- tIndex of Authors -- tIndex of Languages -- tIndex of Subjects0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe extant generalizations about the grammar of space rely heavily on the analyses of declarative sentences. There is a need to check whether these generalizations also hold in the domain of interrogation. To this end this book analyzes data from some 450 languages (including non-standard varieties). The focus is on paradigms of spatial interrogatives such as English where, whither and whence and their internal organization. These paradigms are checked for recurrent patterns of morphological mismatches (such as syncretism) and different degrees of complexity (e.g. the number of segments). The data-base consists of a large parallel literary corpus (Le petit prince and translations thereof) which is complemented by further sources of information such as descriptive grammars. The data are analyzed from a synchronic perspective. However, diachronic issues are addressed unsystematically, too. It is shown that the distribution of phenomena which characterize paradigms of spatial interrogatives are subject to areal-linguistic factors. This is the first typological study of spatial interrogatives. It provides new insights for students of the grammar of space, morphological paradigms, and language typology.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aLinguistics. 4aLinguistik. 4aTypologie. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aConstructional Complexity.  aMorphological Mismatches.  aSpatial Interrogatives.1 aLevkovych, Nataliya, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aNintemann, Julia, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRobbers, Maja, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aUrdze, Aina, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1z978311076249508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Contemporary 2016-2019z978311074297808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PAC